Devex looks at ways technology is helping women and girls be more empowered globally, and makes five recommendations on how to use technology to help achieve the Sustainable Development Goals.

March 8, 2018

CEE Legal Matters: Happy International Women’s Day

Happy International Women’s Day, from all of us at CEE Legal Matters – and a huge thank you for taking the time out of your schedules to join this panel.

Dechert has opened up Spanish-speaking offices in Madrid and Mexico City, successfully completing a pivot from English to Spanish, which took 2.5 years of effort. An international expansion was difficult for a U.S.-based law firm at the time, but today “it is happening across the board,” said Juan Báez Frederking, who heads up the Mexico City office and was the law firm’s first Spanish-speaking lawyer.

The IFLR1000 Index has expanded to include a ranking for legal boutique practices. Six firms listed in a new Boutique Firm ranking made the 2018 Women in Business Law special report unofficially as finalists, based on the number and diversity of deals completed by members of the firm’s leadership teams.
